<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174460>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A – C Scleroplax granulata Rathbun, 1893 (female, cl 4.2 mm, cb 6.0 mm., El Coyote estuary, Abreojos Point, Baja California Sur, México, UABC); D) Pinnixa sp. (female, cb = 6.0 mm, El Verde estuary, Mazatlán, Sinaloa, México, EMU- 842; E) Auxtinixa cristata Rathbun, 1900, (male cb 6.3 mm., St. Lucie, Florida, USA, USNM). A, E) dorsal view; B) WL 1 – 4; C – D) MXP 3. Illustrations not to scale. Dotted lines indicate the setae of the propodus and dactylus. (E from Manning and Felder, 1989)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174460/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

